@NODE "Description"

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Description @{fg text}@{bg back}

Ami-PlayMOD is a command-line program that decodes an Amiga ProTracker MOD file and outputs it on an AHI sound device.
ProTracker MOD is the most popular music format on the Amiga.

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Requirements @{fg text}@{bg back}

- M68020 CPU
- AmigaOS 3.x
- AHI Audio system 4.x
- stack size >= 8192 bytes

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Usage @{fg text}@{bg back}

No particular installation is needed, you should be able to run the utility anywhere in your system.
Binary executable is provided in the "Bin" directory.
I have included a few MOD files in the "MOD" directory.



Run with no arguments to see the following usage message:

Ami-PlayMOD V1.0 - 17/04/2009
Amiga ProTracker MOD player
by   Massimiliano Scarano   mscarano@libero.it

Usage:
> Ami-PlayMOD MyFavouriteMODFile



How to run:
1) > stack 8192
2) > Ami-PlayMOD MyFavouriteMODFile
   - Select AHI audio driver and mixing rate   @{"   See example   " link "Gfx/ahi-requester.ilbm/main"}
   - CTRL-C to exit

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Features @{fg text}@{bg back}

- done with ProTracker V1.1B by Lars Hamre in mind
- plays [M.K.] MOD files with 31 samples (8 bits) and 4 channels
- written in C language from scratch, source code supplied
- Amiga sound preserved with high accuracy, use of ProTracker tables
- easy to port to any sound device (mobile phones, portable gaming consoles, ...), OS dependent stuff well marked
- tested OK with Mungwall and Enforcer
- AmigaGuide documentation
- a few MOD files supplied

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Used platform @{fg text}@{bg back}

Developed and tested on:
* Cloanto Amiga Forever 2006 Premium Edition, WinUAE 1.2.0, JIT, TCP/IP
* Some AmigaOS 3.9 and AmigaOS 3.5 files, ROM 3.1
* Kickstart 45.57, Workbench 45.3 (12/07/2001)
* System: 68020 68881 (INST: Cache)
* SAS/C Amiga Compiler 6.58 Copyright (c) 1988-1995 SAS Institute Inc.
* 1024 x 768 Workbench screen with 65536 colours (16 bit)
* ahi.device 5.33 (04/12/2003) )1994-2003 Martin Blom. 68020 version.

Also tested with Cloanto Amiga Forever 2008 Premium Edition.

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Source code @{fg text}@{bg back}

Project files are located in the "Source" directory.

Compile with
"sc link Ami-PlayMOD_V1_0_YYYYMMDD.c"

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Future improvements @{fg text}@{bg back}

- better effects accuracy (?)
- GUI (?)

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Notes @{fg text}@{bg back}

* Execute this Shell command to check which version of ahi.device you have:
  > version full System:Devs/ahi.device

* Some MOD files loop, use CTRL-C to exit.

* Have a look at the source code for technical details.

